com.examle.ex4_vitaly.list

Class ListImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.examle.ex4_vitaly.list.ListImpl

  • public final class ListImpl
extends java.lang.Object
    In this class all tasks about List are implemented. a. Enumeration - reading list values. The List will be output with Enumeration enumerationOutput() and using List.toString outputBeans(). b. Iterator - reading and removing elements from the list. Two features were demonstrated in iteratorDeleteByAge(int) and iteratorOutput(). c. ListIterator - reading next and previous values, removing, updating and adding new element. The implementation is in following methods: listIteratorDeleteByAge(int), listIteratorAdd(Bean), listIteratorOutput(), listIteratorSetByAge(Bean, int). d. Comparable allows objects to be comparable and sort them in specified order. Bean class implements Comparable c. Comparator interface allows to create own Comparator by which the objects will be sorted. BeanNameComparator is an example of Comparator for Bean class.
